Summer holidays mean more time spent around water, whether at beaches, lakes, rivers or pools. It's also is a time of increased drownings, with a number of incidents already recorded over the last few weeks. The National Sea Rescue Institute continues to be on high alert. Spokesperson Craig Lambinon has more details. #dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three girls have drowned at Kenton-on-Sea in the Eastern Cape. A search is underway for a young boy who has gone missing. READ: Snake Park Drownings | Three bodies recovered in a stream The National Sea Rescue Institute spokesperson Craig Lambinon is urging caution as thousands enjoy their December holidays in coastal areas. "We appeal to the public for that safety-conscious mindset around water at all times," he said. Watch the video above for more details.